 a sense that matters of science stand outside the contingencies of language and the influences of rhetoric.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCommunication in sciencexPhilosophy. 0aGenetics. 0aRhetoricxPhilosophy. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aLanguage Arts : Composition and Rhetoric Studies. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Science and Society. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Science and Technology. 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147851640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791478516423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791478516/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles